Since $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{c}$ lie in the $xy$-plane, $\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c}$ is a vector pointing in the positive $z$-direction.  Hence,
\[\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} = \|\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c}\| \mathbf{k} = 7 \sqrt{2} \cos \angle AOC \mathbf{k}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{c} &= \frac{\mathbf{c} \cdot \mathbf{a}}{\|\mathbf{a}\|^2} \mathbf{a} + \frac{\mathbf{c} \cdot \mathbf{b}}{\|\mathbf{b}\|^2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{(\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c}) \cdot \mathbf{b}}{(\|\mathbf{a}\| \|\mathbf{b}\|)^2} (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}) \\
&= \sqrt{2} \cos \angle AOC \mathbf{a} + \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \mathbf{b} + \frac{7 \sqrt{2} \cos \angle AOC (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}) \cdot \mathbf{b}}{2} \\
&= \sqrt{2} \cos \angle AOC \mathbf{a} + \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \mathbf{b}.
\end{align*}Hence, $(m,n) = \boxed{\left( \sqrt{2} \cos \angle AOC, \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \right)}.$

